**Use `defineComponent` with Explicit Typings (Vue 3)**

If you're using Vue 3, you can explicitly define types for the `data()` method using `defineComponent`. Here's an example of how to do it:

```typescript
<script lang="ts">
import { defineComponent } from 'vue';

export default defineComponent({
  data(): { 
    hellStringType: string; 
    hellNumberType: number; 
    hellInvalid: string; 
  } {
    return {
      hellStringType: this.getNumber(),
      hellNumberType: this.getNumber(),
      hellInvalid: this.buildSomethingElse(),
    };
  },
  methods: {
    getNumber(): number {
      return 42;
    },
    buildSomethingElse(): string {
      // Return a valid value to match the type
      return 'Valid string';
    }
  }
});
</script>
```

This solution will allow TypeScript to infer and validate types in your Vue components correctly. It ensures the `data()` method is correctly typed, and also ensures that method calls within `data()` are type-checked properly.

